1
00:00:00,050 --> 00:00:01,319
Day 8.

2
00:00:01,319 --> 00:00:09,694
I did the thing that made my stomach hurt for three days — I wrote 1200 words called Why I Was Wrong For 7 Days.

3
00:00:09,694 --> 00:00:11,069
I can't code.

4
00:00:11,069 --> 00:00:13,222
9 years in crypto.

5
00:00:13,222 --> 00:00:15,416
AI trades my thousand.

6
00:00:15,416 --> 00:00:16,736
Day 8.

7
00:00:16,736 --> 00:00:19,902
Yesterday I tore the strategy up.

8
00:00:19,902 --> 00:00:25,791
Today I had to tell everyone who'd been following — with the real numbers attached, no polish.

9
00:00:25,791 --> 00:00:28,625
First paragraph was the hardest.

10
00:00:28,625 --> 00:00:31,611
After that the sentences wrote themselves.

11
00:00:31,611 --> 00:00:33,750
You know what I was most afraid of?

12
00:00:33,750 --> 00:00:36,638
People thinking I was less credible.

13
00:00:36,638 --> 00:00:38,875
Turns out the opposite is true.

14
00:00:38,875 --> 00:00:46,430
People trust you not because you never make mistakes — but because you'll say so in front of real numbers when you do.

15
00:00:46,430 --> 00:00:52,708
The moment you publicly admit you were wrong, you're a year ahead of everyone who stayed silent.

16
00:00:52,708 --> 00:00:55,041
Because silence compounds.

17
00:00:55,041 --> 00:00:56,845
Mistakes compound.

18
00:00:56,845 --> 00:01:02,319
Public correction is the only thing that flips that second one into something useful.

19
00:01:02,319 --> 00:01:06,777
Day 9 tomorrow — I walked away from the screen for the first time.

20
00:01:06,777 --> 00:01:08,125
Follow along.

